<title type="html"><![CDATA[Four Score adapters incompatible with most controllers?...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=235&amp;p=1536#p1536"><![CDATA[
it's quite possible that some of your controllers have a bad IC chip.<br />I once builded a NES to PC gameport adapter and one of my<br />4 controllers didn't worked with it, i replaced the IC chip and it worked fine.<br /><br />My adapter used CD4017 to emulate P/S line, 4000 series cannot produce<br />more current than 1mA, but in real NES the P/S line output current is in fact<br />larger.<br /><br />If i remember correctly, NES four score has built in autofire options,<br />so it might be that the exhausted IC is overloading the your four player device.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=61">sepi</a> — Sat Mar 12, 2005 11:35 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
